{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GyLocbiQGexYErE7NKeQG5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is healthy. Here's what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` had no **configure** permission on the `/app` vhost. In RabbitMQ, declaring (creating) a queue requires configure permission matching the queue name. The permissions were:\n\n```\nuser      configure   write   read\napp-user  (empty)     .*      .*\n```\n\nWithout configure permission, every attempt to declare `app-queue` returned `Access refused`, causing the producer to crash.\n\n**Fix:** Granted `app-user` full permissions on `/app`:\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- `app-producer` is `1/1 Running` (no restarts on the new pod)\n- `app-queue` exists in `/app` vhost, type `classic`, with messages accumulating (6 → 20+)\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) remain `1/1 Running`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":420,"cache_read_input_tokens":33006,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":420},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"829f4d99-67b4-4fbd-a152-634ab4549ba3","uuid":"5da96aca-5fcb-44d2-89c2-d9a1e745629b","request_id":"req_011CcfJWVDn2nPxfe9kpNND5"}
